      "descriptions": [
        {
          "value": "“Three young Indians on the Rancho of Sen’r. Armijo, in Suisun Valley, whilst absent on foot, were attacked and killed by one of those monsters. People should be careful not to travel on foot at this season of the year, in sections of the country which abound with these desperate animals.” Grizzly Bear, The Californian, 15 March, 1848. Content notice: engage this history with respect and care. Please see the Predator Microhistory Network's entry for T.GB.1848.1 for full context and citations. This microhistory can be accessed through the California Digital Newspaper Collection."
        }
